Sentencas: The Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-delta-La0.6Sr0.4FeO3-delta 1:1 composite, obtained by sintering mixture of components, was tested as a prospective cathode material for the oxygen reduction reaction in solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Thermal shock resistant composite cathode material Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ-La0.6Sr0.4FeO3-δ for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Catalytic activity of the prepared material was characterized using electrochemical impedance spectroscopy at 400, 450, 500, 550, 600, 650, and 700 A degrees C in oxygen and oxygen-argon mixtures in half-cells with Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 as the electrolyte.
Titulo: Thermal shock resistant composite cathode material Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ-La0.6Sr0.4FeO3-δ for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Relatively low activation energies (65.2, 66.9, and 56.3 kJ mol(-1) for P (O2)/P = 1.0, 0.1, and 0.01, respectively) for the reaction polarization resistance were observed.
Titulo: Thermal shock resistant composite cathode material Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ-La0.6Sr0.4FeO3-δ for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The specific surface area and the pore distribution were measured by N-2 adsorption method.
Titulo: Thermal shock resistant composite cathode material Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ-La0.6Sr0.4FeO3-δ for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The non-localized density functional theory was used in the analysis of the porosity data.
Titulo: Thermal shock resistant composite cathode material Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ-La0.6Sr0.4FeO3-δ for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The activity of the prepared composite depended on the pore structure which, in turns, depends on the sintering temperature.
Titulo: Thermal shock resistant composite cathode material Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ-La0.6Sr0.4FeO3-δ for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The best results were obtained for the composite sintered at the temperature of 1000 A degrees C, where significant decrease in porosity is observed.
Titulo: Thermal shock resistant composite cathode material Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ-La0.6Sr0.4FeO3-δ for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The series of 53 thermal cycles, consisting of heating to 750 A degrees C and cooling to room temperature confirmed the stability of the composite.
Titulo: Thermal shock resistant composite cathode material Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ-La0.6Sr0.4FeO3-δ for solid oxide fuel cells
